giraffe.library/G_CloseLayer

    NAME
	G_CloseLayer -- shuts down a layer from use.

    SYNOPSIS
	void G_CloseLayer( G_Layer a0:layer );

    FUNCTION
	Closes all resources used by the layer for clipping.  This
	ends the users access to the layer.  The pointer remains valid
	until the internal
	usecount reaches zero (by G_DropLayer()).  It will then be removed
	from the layer tree.  During this time, its cliplist has
	been destroyed so that it cannot be mapped again.

    INPUTS
	layer -- a valid layer pointer.

    SEE ALSO
	G_OpenLayer(), G_DropLayer()

giraffe.library/G_CycleLayer

    NAME
	G_CycleLayer -- change the depth of a layer.

    SYNOPSIS
	void G_CycleLayer( G_Layer a0:layer );

    FUNCTION
	Moves a layer within its sibling list.  If the layer is behind
	another, it is pulled to the front.  If in the front, it is
	pushed to the back.  Any layers affected by the move are
	automatically updated.

    INPUTS
	layer -- a valid layer pointer.

    SEE ALSO
