giraffe.library/G_DisownLayer

    NAME
	G_DisownLayer -- relinquish control of layer to its parent.

    SYNOPSIS
	BOOL G_DisownLayer( G_Layer a0:layer );

    FUNCTION
	  This sets a flag within the layer so that when its parent
	is closed, it will be also.  Because this is like an indirect
	call to G_CloseLayer(), the pointer is no longer available
	unless a call to G_UseLayer() has also been made.  This 
	function is useful for making a whole tree of layers that
	can be closed with one function call.
	  This function should only be called by the task that called 
	G_OpenLayer().  Because the function cannot tell the 
	difference, it's up to you.

    INPUTS
	layer -- layer pointer returned by G_OpenLayer()
 
    RESULT
	returns TRUE if the call was a success.

    BUGS

    SEE ALSO
	G_OwnLayer(), G_UseLayer, G_DropLayer

