giraffe.library/G_LockLayer

    NAME
	G_LockLayer -- gain exclusive access to a layer.

    SYNOPSIS
	void G_LockLayer( G_Layer a0:layer );

    FUNCTION
	This obtains an internal semaphore on a layer for exclusive
	control and also gets a shared lock on the layer tree so
	that the hierarchy won't be changed.
	  If the layer has already been locked using locklayers(),
	this lock will be made global.  Note: this cannot be done
	the other way around.  A call to locklayer() before 
	locklayers() will result in a freeze.

    INPUTS
	layer -- a valid layer pointer.

    RESULT

    BUGS
	Translation of shared to exclusive lock has not been
	implemented.

    SEE ALSO

giraffe.library/G_LockLayers

    NAME
	G_LockLayers -- get an exclusive lock on the layer tree.

    SYNOPSIS
	void G_LockLayers( G_Layer a0:layer );

    FUNCTION
	This gets an exclusive lock on all the layers in the tree.
	This is used in the example window server when a window is
	being resized and direct drawing into the bitmap is required.

	NOTE: many layer functions make use of these locks and since
	they cannot be used interchangeably, ie. a call to locklayer()
	followed by a call to G_LockLayers() will freeze the system,
	be very careful of their use.


    INPUTS
	layer -- a valid layer pointer.

    NOTE
	  All locks are given in first come first serve order.
	So for example, if a layer is locked but shared, and
	someone else is waiting for an exclusive lock of the
	entire tree, then if a third process just wants a
	shared lock, then it will be forced to wait.

    BUGS

    SEE ALSO

