giraffe.library/G_OpenRootLayer

    NAME
	G_OpenRootLayer -- creates a clipping hierarchy for a bitmap.

    SYNOPSIS
	G_Layer G_OpenRootLayer( E_EBitMapPtr a0:bitmap, struct
TagItem * a1:tags );

    FUNCTION
	Creates a parentless layer that acts as the root for all other
	layers created afterwards.  It is sized to the bounds of the
	bitmap and automatically mapped.  Root layers can use a
	subset of layer tags which make sense for its use.
	   Root layers are destroyed using G_CloseLayer().

    INPUTS
	bitmap -- valid EGS bitmap pointer.
	tags   -- an array of layer tags appropriate for the root.

    RESULT
	root -- pointer to a garp layer.

    SEE ALSO
	G_OpenLayer(), G_CloseLayer()

